==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zinnia
<hw>Zin"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. So called
after Professor <ets>Zinn</ets>, of G⟦oum⟧ttingen.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any plant of the composite genus
<gen>Zinnia</gen>, Mexican herbs with opposite leaves and large
gay-colored blossoms. <spn>Zinnia elegans</spn> is the commonest species
in cultivation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

